                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d476">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/6855</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-16T12:00:00-04:16">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1917, 12 noon</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.20 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your September 13, 5 p.m. Minister of Marine very kindly called at my house last
                    evening and gave me complete list Argentine <pb facs="0500" n="328"
                        xml:id="pg_328"/> merchant marine with their whereabouts, 34 vessels in all
                    not including river steamers. Only 4 exceed 1,000 tons. They are about half on
                    voyage to Brazil, 15 to France. I asked him informally about placing vessels
                    under Argentine flag, subject of course to law requiring one-third crew
                    Argentine, and he said it was perfectly easy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SFJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
